      <billSummaries>
        <item>
          <text><![CDATA[<p><strong>Ensuring Linguistic Excellence and Vocational Aptitude by Teaching English Act or the ELEVATE Act</strong></p> <p>This bill amends the Elementary and Secondary Education Act of 1965 to allow states to count students who relocated&nbsp;from Puerto Rico (where Spanish is the primary language)&nbsp;in their English learner programs for purposes of calculating&nbsp;federal funding for such programs.</p>]]></text>
